          "Limitations"
        ],
        [
          "Classification",
          "Intelligent Tutoring System",
          "Correctectly answering the input question",
          "Correct (1) vs Incorrect (0)",
          "3079 ASSISTments2009 learners, 24768 ASSISTments 2012 learners, 9471 KDDCup learners",
          "ASSISTments",
          "Question Attribtutes, Sequence of Answers",
          "[Question ID, Question/KC Difficulty, KC, Question Discrimination, Input Question Attributes]",
          "Cognitive diagnosis is a form of student modelling in a static setting (i.e. a student’s knowledge state does not change, or is not meant to, during a test).\n\nTest theory methods are interpretable and often evaluate 2 perspectives: ability level or cognition level. \n\nThese features can be valuable additions to DKT model in order to increase its interpretability.\n\n",
          "DCDKT looks to include the cognitive level features into a DKT model.\n\nThis is done in order to incorporate items such as: Difficulty and/or discrimination.",
          "Questions without a Knowledge Component were not considered. Similarly, learners with fewer than 15 answers were disregarded.\n\nStudents wth more than 200 answers were divided into multiple dummy students.\n\n\n\n\n\n",
          "BKT, DKT_Q, DKT_KC, DKT_MLP, DKVMN, DIRT_1, DIRT_2, DIRT_3, DIRT_4, DNeuralCDM_1, DNeuralCDM_2, DNeuralCDM_3, DNeural_CDM_4",
          "Holdout Method",
          "ASSIST09\n{Accuracy: 0.7838 - DNeuralCDM_4, AUC: 0.7471 - DNeuralCDM_4}\n\nASSIST12\n{Accuracy:  0.7780 - DNeuralCDM_3, AUC: 0.7597 - DNeuralCDM_4}\n\nKDDCup\n{Accuracy: 0.8114 - DNeuralCDM_4, AUC: 0.8525 - DNeuralCDM_4}",
          "Predictions were attempted using different possible models: \n\nDKT_Q → only using question features.\n\nDKT_KC: Each question is represented by the KC ID\n\nDKT_MLP: Same input as DKT_KC, but output was produced by 2 feed-forward layers.\n\nThe congnitive diagnosis section is presented using DIRT or DNeuralCDM.\n\nNumber at the end of DIRT or DNeuralCDM represents the type of features being considered for each.\n\n\n1: Question ID, \n2:QID and KC ID, \n3: QID, KC ID, Difficulty, \n4: QID, KC ID, Difficulty, Discrimination ",
          "No cross-validation.\n\nAdd additional educational priors. \n\nModels considered only use GRU.\n\n"
        ]
      ],
      "index": 6
    }
  ],
